# textdomain: mcl_stairs
Stairs are useful to reach higher places by walking over them; jumping is not required. Placing stairs in a corner pattern will create corner stairs. Stairs placed on the ceiling or at the upper half of the side of a block will be placed upside down.=Eskailerak leku altuagoetara iristeko erabilgarriak dira haien gainean ibiltzean; Ez da beharrezkoa salto egitea. Izkina batean eskailerak jartzeak izkinako eskailerak sortuko ditu. Bloke baten aldeko sabaian edo goiko erdian jarritako eskailerak ahuspez jarriko dira.
Double @1=@1 Bikoitza
Slabs are half as high as their full block counterparts and occupy either the lower or upper part of a block, depending on how it was placed. Slabs can be easily stepped on without needing to jump. When a slab is placed on another slab of the same type, a double slab is created.=Lauzak bloke osoko kontraparteen altueren erdiak dira, eta bloke baten behealdea edo goikaldea hartzen dute, jarri den moduaren arabera. Lauzak erraz zapaldu daitezke, jauzi egin beharrik gabe. Lauza bat mota bereko beste lauza batean jartzen denean, lauza bikoitza sortzen da.
Upper @1=Goiko @1
Double slabs are full blocks which are created by placing two slabs of the same kind on each other.=Lauza bikoitzak bloke osoak dira, eta mota bereko bi lauza elkarren gainean jarriz sortzen dira.
